Sometimes life can come at you fast. One minute you're graduating high school, and the next you're filing for retirement. Where does all the time go? Throughout our journey we catalog our lives through the use of Media. We drown ourselves in it. Media becomes a mile marker, a signpost that leads our way back into memories past. Furthermore, Media is a tool. A tool which when used properly can convey information, or promote interaction. Ideas can come alive. Expression can become productivity.

We live in complex times with many changing landscapes. Our world turned out much smaller than we thought. Our locality may remain, yet now the world is just around the corner. In this new landscape we have access to a greater audience, and therefore retain a greater responsibility. The world has learned how to use it's voice, now we must learn how to be easily heard. This is our goal, our ambition.

Sometimes we get lost in the vast media soup. We can forget where we come from, and who we are. That is until we gather up those old videos, play our favorite song, or even flip through an ancient photo album. We all come from somewhere, someplace, sometime. That's why we think locally, and share globally.

Carmody Irish pub is located in downtown Duluth Minnesota overlooking beautiful Lake Superior across from the Sheraton Hotel on the lakeside. The building is in the historic Port-town district and once served as the livery stable for the block. They are a classic Irish Pub, and echo Duluth's past as a port with a decidedly nautical theme.

Pack & Mail Plus is located in the Denfeld Shopping Plaza, in West Duluth Minnesota. They are the only Authorized Shipping Center in Duluth providing all Five Carriers; UPS, FedEx, DHL, SpeeDee and the US Mail, at one location.
Nelson Window Tinting is a family run company located in Prescot Wisconsin. Joe Nelson is a professional who is dedicated to detail. Their prices and quality are the best available.

Top Notch Paint Trix was a painting company ran by a friend of ours. The company no longer is established, yet Steve James still airbrushes. A wonderfull artist and a great buisness, they remain a pride to our company.

This was a proposal site for Twin Ports Technology Center & Digital Security Systems. The simple style helps the user navigate easier and supplies a great deal of information pertaining to the buisness. With less clutter to get in your customers way you can focus on selling your product.
